@page "/docs/extensions/reporting/layout"

<Seo Canonical="/docs/extensions/reporting/layout" Title="Blazorise Reporting layout" Description="Define report pages, bands, panels, fields, lines, rectangles, and layout tables in Blazorise Reporting." />

<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/Reporting/Layout" AddedVersion="New">
    Reporting layout
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Reports are organized into bands. Page setup controls the printed document size, and report elements are positioned in measurement units suitable for print.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Page and bands">
        Use report header, page header, detail, report footer, and page footer bands to define where content appears. A panel groups related elements so they can be positioned and moved as one container.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent Code="ReportingLayoutBandsExample" Outlined FullWidth>
        <ReportingLayoutBandsExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Panels
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    A <Code Tag>ReportPanel</Code> is a positioned container for other report elements. Child coordinates are relative to the panel, and elements can be moved into or out of the panel in the designer.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Layout table">
        Tables are layout containers for aligning other report elements. They do not repeat data by themselves.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent Code="ReportingLayoutTableExample" Outlined FullWidth>
        <ReportingLayoutTableExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Lines
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Line elements use <Code>X</Code> and <Code>Y</Code> for placement, <Code>Width</Code> and <Code>Height</Code> for the selectable element box, and <Code>Thickness</Code> for the centered stroke width in points.
    Set <Code>Orientation</Code> to <Code>Orientation.Horizontal</Code> or <Code>Orientation.Vertical</Code> to control the direction of the line.
</DocsPageParagraph>

